<paragraph id="90EFBABF247E0090EED9670E871CD592" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="76D5E80BE02B1587DE1BAAE973833260" bold="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Type.</emphasis>
Mexico: Tamaulipas, Matamoros, April 1831, 
<emphasis id="85945A69525471611A0C32B28028B8C0" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">J. L. Berlandier 2313</emphasis>
(Holotype: G; Isotypes: BM, K, P).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BA5B24E2361CC66D82243B85A77E07E6" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
Plant rhizomatous, perennial, forming extensive colonies, strigillose and often also villous. Stems 20-60(-120) cm tall, sometimes strict with a single unbranched main 
<pageBreakToken id="4BE034F397B86D384C46DBBC2FC2F82A" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" start="start">stem</pageBreakToken>
but usually somewhat decumbent with several branches from the base and usually irregular branching above. Leaves in a basal rosette and cauline, 0.5-7.5 (-9.5) 
<normalizedToken id="C1E577829A8E1F3D2A1E6B6079D143E6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-2.2 cm; subsessile; blade narrowly lanceolate to elliptic, margin subentire to shallowly sinuate-dentate. Inflorescence a spike. Flowers 4-merous, zygomorphic, opening near sunset; floral tube 4-14 mm; sepals 7-11(-14) mm; petals white, fading red, 6-10 mm; staminal filaments 4-8.5 mm, anthers 3-6 mm; style 12-26 mm. Capsule 7-13 
<normalizedToken id="A67D6CCE0CB988DE69695087D9299FC2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm, erect, the body ellipsoid or ovoid, 4-angled, distal half pyramidal, the base of the pyramidal portion distinctly bulging, then immediately and sharply constricted to the terete proximal part. Seeds (2-)3-4(-8), 2-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="69BDDF09DBA689AB6E5E56325C349817" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.25 mm, ovoid, usually flattened on one or several sides by crowding in the fruit, reddish brown. 2n = 28.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="888686DA3EB9E497D0074E99804A5E43" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" type="phenology and distribution">
<paragraph id="CDD8CF619AD623897638E40A602BE0B7" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Phenology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD422520F561BF130DC1752A028CA954" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
Flowering from May through July, but sporadically as late as November. 
<taxonomicName id="3281597B276ED0FAB0192B6D4901CE2E" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="1E43AA92F0044F68171EE964AF547993" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in sandy loam soils from the eastern half of Texas south through Mexico as far south Oaxaca. It is naturalized in Arkansas (Sevier Co.), coastal southern California, Georgia (Glynn Co.); its current status in both Arkansas and Georgia should be verified. It is considered an invasive species in California.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD9D3C570394E33D2A009077A5946EBC" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="449340B4F1C4060CB04EABCBA6F3EFD9" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="DEFDD965D50CBC42A56172749128856F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the sole member of 
<taxonomicName id="BE7A304A19048E19F45B4A9A04F07DE1" authority="Xenogaura" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera subsp. subsection" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" section="Gaura" species="hispida" subSection="Xenogaura" subSpecies="subsection">Oenothera sect. Gaura subsection Xenogaura</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="E04E29D35EF797AA3B77082FD62BC153" author="Raven, PH" journalOrPublisher="Mem. Torrey Bot. Club" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 96" refId="B6" refString="Raven, PH, Gregory, DP, 1972. A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae). Mem. Torrey Bot. Club 23: 1 - 96" title="A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae)." volume="23" year="1972">Raven and Gregory (1972)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="B0FC1AA4863D7EB9247876BCBB64EC6D" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="3AA67A3CDB5CBAB9F87D91020105E96B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
arose following interspecific hybridization between 
<taxonomicName id="DDA43FB6F3D9AEFB0D232A9841169B4C" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Ser." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera suffrutescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis id="D2DD342D39FD03B883F1FB7D2B1FAFA8" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ser.) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch (subsect. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F1BB90E38BA9752336412987BA94DF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Campogaura">
<emphasis id="ADE777D53F088E3D2FF1AE402C10EAD9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Campogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(P. H. Raven &amp; D. P. Gregory) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch) and a species in subsect. 
<taxonomicName id="448690DF08118FEBEB7818F0A0BC4C1F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Stipogaura">
<emphasis id="3BD5C8ABA6EC82BB6186F535ABEF864D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Stipogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(P. H. Raven &amp; D. P. Gregory) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch, possibly near 
<taxonomicName id="5E98F096E96A66F0DE7A7D5BA7A91B6B" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Munz" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera mckelveyae" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mckelveyae">
<emphasis id="44501D2BDE511E633F2178ED7BAAE951" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera mckelveyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Munz) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch. 
<bibRefCitation id="283EB993FBEAD3137811F9E527928E52" author="Hoggard, GD" journalOrPublisher="Amer. J. Bot." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="139 - 148" publicationUrl="10.3732/ajb.91.1.139" refId="B3" refString="Hoggard, GD, Kores, PJ, Molvray, M, Hoggard, RK0, 2004. The phylogeny of Gaura (Onagraceae) based on ITS, ETS and TrnL-F sequence data. Amer. J. Bot. 91: 139 - 148, DOI: 10.3732/ajb.91.1.139" title="The phylogeny of Gaura (Onagraceae) based on ITS, ETS and TrnL-F sequence data." url="10.3732/ajb.91.1.139" volume="91" year="2004">Hoggard et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
found that the pistillate parent of 
<taxonomicName id="1D1855873592410192642D3AD4B96FCC" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="D66A2302429C908F143159B5DA13E139" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was indeed 
<taxonomicName id="E07956D8B7A1A4352ACF3524E163747F" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Munz" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera mckelveyae" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mckelveyae">
<emphasis id="A1576FA68F7EB810B84098297138925B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera mckelveyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a close relative, but that the staminate parent probably came from a lineage related to 
<taxonomicName id="D6300909A95F665C7AF24EF5713EF354" authorityName="Krakos &amp; W. L. Wagner" authorityYear="2013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera dodgeniana" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dodgeniana">
<emphasis id="087AB609942E621F0602A05ECA51CAF0" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera dodgeniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Krakos &amp; W.L.Wagner or 
<taxonomicName id="6296065F5C5D863B2B444154930BEBCF" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Engelm. &amp; A. Gray" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera lindheimeri" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindheimeri">
<emphasis id="D72F11C893672DFBF6EFDAA8BF6FA28C" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera lindheimeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Engelm. &amp; A.Gray) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch in subsect. 
<taxonomicName id="ADAF14DD74D5D4A003A6C902CC94BF6D" authorityName="W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Gaura">
<emphasis id="134633E4CF0B58C80BE813EF6E14CB31" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Gaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) W.L.Wagner &amp; Hoch. 
<taxonomicName id="B637290971A1F5F3278E1E9CF6DDB54C" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="3F327FEA67C7DE20B2EA44BCE8AD895C" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not easily distinguished morphologically from 
<taxonomicName id="E74E0CDC60D55C81F9903081B61F38AA" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Ser." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera suffrutescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis id="F0B4784A34D02DEA387F5F011B8E48AF" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subsect. 
<taxonomicName id="36E52A3F790049737B017DC3758C4277" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSection" subSection="Campogaura">
<emphasis id="98E39F0B77296FCDF8301BD35EBE9C85" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Campogaura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), with which it shares the character of a thick stipe, and occasionally hydridizes in Texas. 
<taxonomicName id="3E011334AD91601FA69B6D62E47D6BAE" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="2ACEDCB30F2486DC88285531C173A03E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an aggressively rhizomatous perennial with fruits conspicuously bulging on the distal half (
<bibRefCitation id="CE4E1A9F5A84E631149FC9DB321508AC" author="Raven, PH" journalOrPublisher="Mem. Torrey Bot. Club" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 96" refId="B6" refString="Raven, PH, Gregory, DP, 1972. A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae). Mem. Torrey Bot. Club 23: 1 - 96" title="A revision of the genus Gaura (Onagraceae)." volume="23" year="1972">Raven and Gregory 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Since 
<taxonomicName id="EA48E646AAEE6970404FDF17373E3FB8" authorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera hispida" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="B25AD6D5E338BDD3A532FB12C36E83D3" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9EB91F8D24402F79321C1B514C62DC1C" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Ser." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Oenothera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Oenothera suffrutescens" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis id="4634FF1220096294A158082AE8F3D932" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Oenothera suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be difficult to distinguish we have included a capsule of the latter in the figure (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5AC3B12F21E66FDD246AF776E4912B55" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Oenothera hispida (Bentham) W. L. Wagner, Hoch &amp; Zarucchi A Habit, Mexico, Nuevo Leon, Roybal 34 (US) B Flower, lateral view, Roybal 34 (US) C Flower, face view, digital image (Ray Pistrum as &quot; Gaura drummondii fresh flower &quot; [http: // redsgoodvsevilcowbarn. blogspot. com / 2012 / 06 / chigger-chow-and-gaura-drummondii. html]) D Base of staminal filaments showing basal scales, Roybal 34 (US) E Capsule, Texas, Hall 213 (US) F Oenothera suffrutescens (Ser.) W. L. Wagner &amp; Hoch capsule, New Mexico, Standley 6481 (US)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.50.4886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/44197" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">1</figureCitation>
-F) for comparison of key features for correct separation of the two species. The rhizomatous habit makes this species potentially invasive, despite its self-incompatibility, but so far it has established itself most aggressively only in coastal southern California (
<bibRefCitation id="90500342DBABD9969EDEC40DB9B1CFC5" author="Wagner, WL" journalOrPublisher="Syst. Bot. Monogr." pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 240" refId="B7" refString="Wagner, WL, Hoch, PC, Raven, PH, 2007. Revised classification of the Onagraceae. Syst. Bot. Monogr. 83: 1 - 240" title="Revised classification of the Onagraceae." volume="83" year="2007">Wagner et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). There are no other Hartweg collections of this species that anyone has seen other than the one cited above as the type collection. We have seen the holotype as an image on the Kew web site that was mistakenly filed under 
<taxonomicName id="3639219151F3B5F0E62BD3B0C458C3CC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Gaura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gaura coccinea" order="Myrtales" pageId="2" pageNumber="27" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis id="49CAA9938C7057B49AC3DC5164A98507" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">Gaura coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pursh. The label information corresponds to the published locality given and is marked as in the Bentham herbarium.
</paragraph>
